* Debian <code>{{Stable project version based on Debian codename}}</code> installed.
* User account <code>user</code> exists.

Become root. <ref>
One way or another.
</ref>

{{CodeSelect|code=
su
}}

Install <code>sudo</code> and </code>adduser</code> package.
<!-- WIKI EDITORS NOTE:
Can use template Install_Package because that would use sudo which is not installed at this point.
-->

{{Box|text=
'''1.''' Update the package lists.

{{CodeSelect|code=
apt update
}}

'''2.''' Upgrade the system.

{{CodeSelect|code=
apt full-upgrade
}}

'''3.''' Install <code>sudo</code> and </code>adduser</code> package.

{{CodeSelect|code=
apt install --no-install-recommends sudo adduser
}}
}}

The following commands need to be run either by root or use <code>sudo</code>. <ref>
Required to use full path to <code>addgroup</code>, <code>adduser</code>, <code>reboot</code> because when using <code>su</code> the <code>PATH</code> environment variable is not adjusted for use with root rights. See <code>echo "$PATH"</code>.

user rights <code>PATH</code>:

<pre>
/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/local/games:/usr/games
</pre>

root rights <code>PATH</code>:

<pre>
/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin
</pre>

When using <code>sudo</code> using /full/path/to/application is not required.
</ref>

Create group <code>console</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
/usr/sbin/addgroup --system console
}}

Add user <code>user</code> to group <code>console</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
/usr/sbin/adduser user console
}}

Add user <code>user</code> to group <code>sudo</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
/usr/sbin/adduser user sudo
}}

Reboot.

{{CodeSelect|code=
/sbin/reboot
}}
